{
  "info": {
    "name": "GPS.id Vendor API + Webhook",
    "description": "GPS.id integration for SWAT Phase 7 — REGENERATED from the live vendor docs (https://gpsid.readme.io, read 2026-06-29).\n\nTwo directions:\n1. **Pull API** (SWAT → GPS.id) — base `https://portal.gps.id/backend/seen/public`. Auth: `POST /login` with the GPS.id portal username+password returns a JWT at `message.data.token`, valid **24h**; send it as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every other call (the collection-level Bearer auth does this; the Login request runs a test script that captures the token into the `gpsidToken` env var automatically). If the vendor rejects `Bearer`, some endpoints accept the raw token — switch the collection auth to a plain `Authorization: {{gpsidToken}}` header.\n2. **Inbound Webhook** (GPS.id → SWAT) — GPS.id PUSHes JSON every ~30s/unit to SWAT's webhook (registered out-of-band by emailing it.ss@gps.id, subject 'Register Endpoint Push Data'). Secured by SWAT's secret path token (`GPS_WEBHOOK_TOKEN`) + IP allowlist + rate-limit + audit. Use the simulator requests to exercise SWAT ingestion without the real vendor.\n\n**Response envelope:** success `{ \"status\": true, \"message\": { \"data\": ... } }`; error `{ \"status\": false, \"message\": \"<reason>\" }`. HTTP 200 ok / 400 failed.\n\n**Rate limits (vendor):** Login 5/10min · Vehicle list 5/5min · Vehicle Detail 2/1min · History 5/5min · Mileage 5/5min.\n\nSet the `GPS.id (vendor)` environment first.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{gpsidToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (get 24h bearer token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.be.true);",
                  "",
                  "// Real envelope: { status, message: { data: { token } } }",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "const token = json?.message?.data?.token;",
                  "if (token) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('gpsidToken', token);",
                  "  console.log('gpsidToken set (24h validity).');",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.warn('No token at message.data.token — check credentials/response.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/login",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["login"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{gpsidUsername}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{gpsidPassword}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "POST {baseUrl}/login → 200 `{ status:true, message:{ data:{ username, fullname, email, phone, token } } }`. Token (JWT) is valid 24h. Wrong creds → 400 `{ status:false, message:'Invalid Credential.' }`. Rate limit: 5 attempts / 10 min."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Vehicles",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Vehicle (list / overview)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/vehicle",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["vehicle"]
            },
            "description": "All registered units → `message.total` + `message.data[]` of { imei, owner, device_name, plate, gsm_no, activation_time, expired_gsm, gps_type, vehicle_type, longitude, latitude, speed, address, last_positioning }. Rate limit 5/5min."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Vehicle Detail (by IMEI)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/vehicle/detail/{{imei}}",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["vehicle", "detail", "{{imei}}"]
            },
            "description": "Single-device detail → message.data { imei, plate, acc, longitude, latitude, angle, speed, mileage, address, door, temperature, last_positioning, last_update, ... }. Rate limit 2/1min (most restrictive)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Reports",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Data History (track points)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/report/history?page=1&per_page=10&device={{imei}}&start={{gpsidStart}}&end={{gpsidEnd}}",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["report", "history"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "per_page", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "device", "value": "{{imei}}", "description": "single IMEI" },
                {
                  "key": "start",
                  "value": "{{gpsidStart}}",
                  "description": "device-timezone start"
                },
                { "key": "end", "value": "{{gpsidEnd}}", "description": "device-timezone end" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Historical breadcrumbs → message.total + message.data[] of { plate, imei, lon, lat, speed, angle, time, acc, battery, fuel, mileage, temperature }. Errors: invalid token/device, start>=end, missing dates. Rate limit 5/5min."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Data Mileage (+ used fuel)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/report/mileage?used_fuel=25.10&device=[{{imei}}]&start={{gpsidStart}}&end={{gpsidEnd}}",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["report", "mileage"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "used_fuel", "value": "25.10", "description": "optional, Km/L" },
                {
                  "key": "device",
                  "value": "[{{imei}}]",
                  "description": "JSON array of IMEIs, MAX 5"
                },
                { "key": "start", "value": "{{gpsidStart}}" },
                { "key": "end", "value": "{{gpsidEnd}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Per-device mileage + fuel → message.data[] of { imei, plate, start, end, mileage, start_mileage, end_mileage, used_fuel_d, used_fuel_total }. `device` is a JSON array (≤5 IMEIs). Errors: 'Device must be a valid JSON string.', 'Device should not be more than 5.', start>=end. Rate limit 5/5min."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Data Parking Report",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/report/parking_report?page=1&per_page=10&device={{imei}}&start={{gpsidStart}}&end={{gpsidEnd}}&min_time=60&max_time=3600",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["report", "parking_report"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "per_page", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "device", "value": "{{imei}}" },
                { "key": "start", "value": "{{gpsidStart}}" },
                { "key": "end", "value": "{{gpsidEnd}}" },
                {
                  "key": "min_time",
                  "value": "60",
                  "description": "optional, min parking secs (default 60)"
                },
                {
                  "key": "max_time",
                  "value": "3600",
                  "description": "optional, max parking secs (default 3600)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Parking events → message.total + message.data[]. Same row shape as history."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Alerts",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Alert Code (reference list)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/ref_alert/alert_code_list",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["ref_alert", "alert_code_list"]
            },
            "description": "Reference map of alert codes → message.data. Use a code as `alert_no` in 'Get History Alert Data'."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get History Alert Data",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/alert/alert_data?page=1&per_page=10&start={{gpsidStart}}&end={{gpsidEnd}}&device={{imei}}&alert_no=",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["alert", "alert_data"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "per_page", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "start", "value": "{{gpsidStart}}" },
                { "key": "end", "value": "{{gpsidEnd}}" },
                { "key": "device", "value": "{{imei}}" },
                {
                  "key": "alert_no",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "alert code from /ref_alert/alert_code_list (blank = all)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Historical alerts for a device in a window, filtered by alert_no."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Commands & Streaming",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Log Command (by IMEI + date)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/command/log/{{imei}}?date={{gpsidDate}}",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["command", "log", "{{imei}}"],
              "query": [{ "key": "date", "value": "{{gpsidDate}}", "description": "YYYY-MM-DD" }]
            },
            "description": "Command history for a tracker on a given date."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "On/Off Engine (relay)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/command/send/{{imei}}?command=RELAY,1%23",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["command", "send", "{{imei}}"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "command",
                  "value": "RELAY,1%23",
                  "description": "Engine OFF = 'RELAY,1#'  ·  Engine ON = 'RELAY,0#' (# URL-encoded as %23)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Cut/restore engine via relay. ⚠ The vendor OpenAPI is ambiguous on where `command` goes (path vs query vs body) — modelled here as a query param; verify against a real unit before relying on it. DANGER: 'RELAY,1#' cuts the engine."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Set Link Monitoring (share location)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/share_location/create_share",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["share_location", "create_share"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"imei\": \"{{imei}}\",\n  \"expiration\": 60\n}"
            },
            "description": "Create a time-limited public share link. Body { imei, expiration } — expiration in MINUTES from generation."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Link Live Streaming Public",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gpsidBaseUrl}}/streaming_with_apikey/streaming_key?imei={{imei}}&channel=1",
              "host": ["{{gpsidBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["streaming_with_apikey", "streaming_key"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "imei", "value": "{{imei}}" },
                { "key": "channel", "value": "1", "description": "camera channel (default 1)" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Public live-stream link for a camera-equipped unit → message.data.link."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Inbound Webhook (simulate GPS.id → SWAT)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Push single ping → SWAT",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{swatRootUrl}}/api/v1/integrations/gps/webhook/{{gpsWebhookToken}}",
              "host": ["{{swatRootUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "integrations", "gps", "webhook", "{{gpsWebhookToken}}"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"VehicleId\": \"{{imei}}\",\n  \"VehicleNumber\": \"L 1234 AB\",\n  \"DatetimeUTC\": \"2026-06-26 03:15:00\",\n  \"GpsLocation\": \"Jl. Ahmad Yani\",\n  \"Lat\": -7.2575,\n  \"Lon\": 112.7508,\n  \"Speed\": 32.5,\n  \"Direction\": 145,\n  \"Engine\": \"ON\",\n  \"Odometer\": 1000250,\n  \"Car_Status\": \"START\",\n  \"VehicleType\": \"truck\",\n  \"Alarm\": \"\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Simulates the GPS.id push payload (Register Endpoint webhook; fields per the vendor doc: VehicleId, VehicleNumber, DatetimeUTC, GpsLocation, Lon/Lat, Speed, Direction, Engine, Odometer, Car_Status, VehicleType, Alarm). token = SWAT's GPS_WEBHOOK_TOKEN (≥16 chars). 200 { accepted:1 }; unknown IMEI → parked in GpsUnmatchedPing. Bad token → 401, disallowed IP → 403, over-rate → 429, future DatetimeUTC → rejected."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Push batch (array) → SWAT",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{swatRootUrl}}/api/v1/integrations/gps/webhook/{{gpsWebhookToken}}",
              "host": ["{{swatRootUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "integrations", "gps", "webhook", "{{gpsWebhookToken}}"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "[\n  {\n    \"VehicleId\": \"{{imei}}\",\n    \"DatetimeUTC\": \"2026-06-26 03:15:00\",\n    \"Lat\": -7.2575,\n    \"Lon\": 112.7508,\n    \"Speed\": 30,\n    \"Direction\": 140,\n    \"Engine\": \"ON\",\n    \"Odometer\": 1000250,\n    \"Car_Status\": \"START\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"VehicleId\": \"{{imei}}\",\n    \"DatetimeUTC\": \"2026-06-26 03:15:30\",\n    \"Lat\": -7.2588,\n    \"Lon\": 112.7521,\n    \"Speed\": 28,\n    \"Direction\": 150,\n    \"Engine\": \"ON\",\n    \"Odometer\": 1000500,\n    \"Car_Status\": \"START\"\n  }\n]"
            },
            "description": "The webhook accepts a single object OR an array → 200 { accepted:n }."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
